.SS FilesAPI
.PP
File and directory operations (accessed via
.B client.files
). All file operations support
.B transfer_method="http"
(default, via API) or
.B transfer_method="sftp"
(direct file transfer).
.TP
.BI client.files.list(path="/", page=1, page_size=100, transfer_method="http")
List files in a remote directory.
.TP
.BI client.files.list_all(path="/", transfer_method="http")
List all files in a directory with automatic pagination.
.TP
.BI client.files.mkdir(path, force=True, transfer_method="http")
Create a remote directory.
.TP
.BI client.files.rename(old_path, new_name)
Rename a file or directory.
.TP
.BI client.files.copy(src_path, dest_dir, transfer_method="http")
Copy a file or directory.
.TP
.BI client.files.move(src_path, dest_dir, transfer_method="http")
Move or rename a file or directory.
.TP
.BI client.files.delete(path, transfer_method="http")
Delete a file or directory.
.TP
.BI client.files.cat(remote_path, head=None, tail=None, start=None, end=None, encoding="utf-8", all_lines=False)
Read selected lines from a remote text file (SFTP only).
.B head : lines from beginning.
.B tail : lines from end.
.B start/end : 1-based line range.
.B all_lines : force output all lines for large files.
.TP
.BI client.files.upload(file_path, remote_path, on_progress=None, chunk_size=104857600, transfer_method="http")
Upload a local file.
.B on_progress : callback(filename, bytes_read, total_bytes).
.TP
.BI client.files.upload_directory(local_dir, remote_dir, on_progress=None, check_exists=None, confirm=None, chunk_size=104857600, transfer_method="http")
Upload an entire directory recursively.
.TP
.BI client.files.download(remote_path, local_path=None, on_progress=None, chunk_size=104857600, transfer_method="http")
Download a remote file.
.B on_progress : callback(filename, bytes_downloaded, total_bytes).
.TP
.BI client.files.download_directory(remote_dir, local_dir, on_progress=None, chunk_size=104857600, transfer_method="http")
Download an entire remote directory recursively.
.TP
.BI client.files.compress(source_dir, target_path)
Compress a remote directory into an archive.
.TP
.BI client.files.uncompress(archive_path, dest_dir, password=None)
Uncompress a remote archive.
.TP
.B client.files.get_confidentiality_levels()
Get available file confidentiality levels.
.TP
.BI client.files.set_confidentiality(path, level)
Set file confidentiality level.
.TP
.B client.files.get_root_dir()
Get root directory information.
.PP
SFTP module (\fBclient.sftp\fP):
.TP
.BI client.sftp.tailf(remote_path, encoding="utf-8")
Run \fBtail -f\fP on a remote file via SSH exec channel. Streams output in
real-time and returns (tail_pid, channel) on exit. Requires
\fBpip install jhinno-appform-sdk[sftp]\fP.
.TP
.BI client.sftp.kill_tail(tail_pid)
Kill a tail process started by tailf() via a new SSH session.
.PP
SFTP configuration is optional. Install with:
.B pip install jhinno-appform-sdk[sftp]
.PP
When using SFTP, all file operations (ls, mkdir, cp, mv, rm, put, get, cat, tailf) work without the API gateway.
